        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 11:12PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1111 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles south of Ronda to 5 miles southeast of
Monroe. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Concord, Salisbury, Mocksville, Kannapolis, China Grove, Spencer,
Granite Quarry, Rockwell, Mt Pleasant, and Bermuda Run.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
